Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper focuses on a language-independent subword tokenizer and detokenizer designed for neural-based text processing, including neural machine translation. 
- cs.LG (Learning): The paper discusses the performance of subword training and segmentation with various configurations, which is related to machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a method for improving neural-based text processing, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper focuses on neural-based text processing, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper does not directly relate to computer vision, it is possible that the subword tokenizer and detokenizer could be applied to text in images, which would fall under this sub-category.
